item.title: Need help with setting server online
item.dc:creator: @Whipz Whipz
item.description:
@Whipz wrote:

[quote=“Ewa Hax, post:1, topic:119467”]Whipz here is how you do it…

To find your ip : Click start then click contol programs. Then going into your network connections. After that click the tab under Lan or high-speed connections. Click support then the ip address bar will be there.

To port-foward : Take your ip address and use that as a address in the internet address bar. Then once your logged into your server , you click some close to : Virtual Servers : then inside there when it asks for a username and password just log in and then fill in your information.

Hope this helped you with your server. Good luck ! Big Grin[/quote]

Thanks man but, where i need to click on start?
